name: Atta
description:
Fourth stop of my Interstellar Journey; I almost flew past this place, the atmosphere is essentially black, but the light of an odd structure caught my attention enough to give it a look. After inspecting it up close, I realized the floor was full of unexpectedly well-kept grass, and the structure was in reality human symbology. Is this what getting my heart pulled out of my body feels like?
